Diff (+1053/-151):
PR DESCRIPTION:
This implements the design that was discussed in https://github.com/smallrye/smallrye-config/issues/215.

It introduces a new `Bootstrap` configuration phase that can be consumed by a Recorder whose intent is to produce a `ConfigSourceProvider`. These recorders are run during runtime init, but before the other Recorders. Their result contributes to the final runtime `Config` creation.

The part I am not too excited about is the integration into the build system since the new build items don't utilize the full power of the build system. However, 1) appropriate error messages are provided so people looking to create a bootstrap config implementation will be properly guided, 2) I don't see a good way of making it better (and avoiding hard-coding the specific Build Items) unless we introduce a new recording phase as well.



